HEADWORD: Chondrule
<hw>Chon"drule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. from Gr. <?/
a grain (of wheat or spelt), cartilage.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
peculiar rounded granule of some mineral, usually enstatite or
chrysolite, found imbedded more or less abundantly in the mass of many
meteoric stones, which are hence called <xex>chondrites</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

